<div id="review_303205339" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/303205339" />
    <a title="Max Ostrovsky" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/151055-max-ostrovsky"><img alt="Max Ostrovsky" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1182971578p2/151055.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/303205339?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Max Ostrovsky" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Max Ostrovsky" href="/user/show/151055-max-ostrovsky">Max Ostrovsky</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780345409324" href="/book/show/481559.Blood_and_Gold">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=pop">pop</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=chick-lit">chick-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/151055-max-ostrovsky?shelf=mythology">mythology</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer303205339" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11771958289754301751">Another book-end story by Rice and no surprises. I&apos;m determined to finish the series, but it is getting tedious. While this book seemed to have an easier prose than most of the Chronicle books (Body Thief aside), the lack of plot or tension or drama or really anything going on kept this book from a higher rating. <br/>That said, and despite all that said, it was a page turner. Rice&apos;s prose in this volume is engaging and forward driven. While not much is actually going on, I was interested in what not</span>
  <span id="freeText11771958289754301751" style="display:none">Another book-end story by Rice and no surprises. I'm determined to finish the series, but it is getting tedious. While this book seemed to have an easier prose than most of the Chronicle books (Body Thief aside), the lack of plot or tension or drama or really anything going on kept this book from a higher rating. <br />That said, and despite all that said, it was a page turner. Rice's prose in this volume is engaging and forward driven. While not much is actually going on, I was interested in what nothing was going to happen next. <br />Ultimately, it was a character piece (a long one) about how Marius learned how anger affects him and why he must keep his anger in check. <br />Too many characters and themes are brought up in this volume that aren't resolved. Since I know there are a couple more to the Chronicles, I hope for some resolution. Without giving away the ending, the resolution of this book was lacking and while it should have been satisfying, it was missing the emotional build up that the book had many opportunities of developing, but never did. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11771958289754301751" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


